{"id": "1407928126427758733", "channel_id": "1407928126427758733", "type": 0, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "Every scene in the game appears to have a separate English subtitle under it, which is usually the same meaning (I presume they are sourced via a different translation and thus don't always line up with the translation right above it).\n\nI presume this originates from Chinese scenes having an English tagline to go along with it, but this creates some conflict in English - either the two taglines both match, and the second one appears to be quite redundant, or the taglines don't match, and a question arises of why the same thing is being said twice.\n\nThe vast majority of these appear to be the same in both instances, but some are quite different from the Chinese - I'm unsure if this is due to liberties taken by machine translation, or if the taglines were handpicked by the narrative team and some are meant to be different. The taglines also don't appear to show up in the spreadsheet - I presume they are hard edited into the image and thus might not be very easy to edit. \n\nGiven this, what is the best course of action? Should we change the English chapter titles to match the English tagline, even if the meaning is quite different? Should we be accepting the English taglines as definitive or should we edit the titles without taking them into account?", "timestamp": "2025-08-21T03:23:43.380000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "👍", "emoji_id": null, "count": 2}], "attachments": [{"id": "1407928126859903046", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 977939, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1407928126427758733/1407928126859903046/image.png?ex=6a32133f&is=6a30c1bf&hm=9c96a3ce3b94773deb87804cae209ccc927e50c29b8c77327f684b55e144e574&"}, {"id": "1407928127472144495", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 987222, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1407928126427758733/1407928127472144495/image.png?ex=6a32133f&is=6a30c1bf&hm=ac4b4895d55c5e093d7c243b9b4d81015298cbdd2b45d2ec6bb31300a87d731a&"}, {"id": "1407928128071794689", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 931533, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1407928126427758733/1407928128071794689/image.png?ex=6a32133f&is=6a30c1bf&hm=b9839ddad621da65916804cc4316512e01d0d9a4f4e0625bd22fc33b91d48114&"}, {"id": "1407928129149734932", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 815825, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1407928126427758733/1407928129149734932/image.png?ex=6a321340&is=6a30c1c0&hm=0dd2baa15590be1d77feb958d0c9762a59be86da500d8fc738ad412ec4e1f379&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1407928126427758733", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Scene Title Cards", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1412867280844357813"], "is_thread_starter": true}
{"id": "1407928531547328613", "channel_id": "1407928126427758733", "type": 0, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "I also noticed that in the side events, the chapter title above it is the name of the side event, but again that doesn't always line up with the existing English chapter name. Example from Ogier's:", "timestamp": "2025-08-21T03:25:19.968000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1407928531257659503", "filename": "image.png", "content_type": "image/png", "size": 1175958, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1407928126427758733/1407928531257659503/image.png?ex=6a32139f&is=6a30c21f&hm=a5ce7df95787bb502796c2b3c293e9a073c2b39f64c6e045b06e8aba8ac0ada9&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1407928126427758733", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Scene Title Cards", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1407929137439441058", "channel_id": "1407928126427758733", "type": 0, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "①: The title card displays \"A Knight's Wish\", but the ingame title of the chapter is \"The Knight's Wish\". Not much of a difference for Ogier, but differences are larger for some other stories (Ramona: Timeworn is \"One Step Away\" vs \"One Step Closer\", Kathigu-ra is \"Everburning Vex\" vs \"Immortality Sun\", Miryam event story is \"Desecrate\" vs \"Blasphemy\", etc)\n\n②: This is the actual scene translation text located in the spreadsheet, but the same text shows up in multiple instances and thus there are multiple translations for each scene - it's difficult to track down all instances and ensure they stay consistent. I have noticed at least 4 instances of every single chapter title's appearance - once in the main story text preceding the actual text in the scene (this determines the text that shows up here), and then once for each of the difficulty levels in the \"Stage Details\" popup that shows up before you enter a stage - normal, hard, and madness (unimplemented). These scene names show up in the English term spreadsheet as well, meaning there is a minimum of 5 locations that every scene title needs to be updated in in order to stay consistent, and I don't know which one to use as a definitive source.\n\n③: This is the English tagline which does not show up anywhere in the spreadsheet and is usually the same as the title, but you can see in this particular instance of Ogier that the tagline (\"A Dream Within a Dream\") is quite different from the actual scene title (「梦，或理想」, \"Dreams, or Ideals\")", "timestamp": "2025-08-21T03:27:44.424000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-08-21T03:32:26.623000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1407928126427758733", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Scene Title Cards", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1407931964618706954", "channel_id": "1407928126427758733", "type": 0, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "(that said, this is all somewhat nit-picky stuff - if the answer is as simple as \"it doesn't really matter, we don't care if it's inconsistent\", just let me know and I don't mind moving on)", "timestamp": "2025-08-21T03:38:58.476000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1407928126427758733", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Scene Title Cards", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1407943272789446746", "channel_id": "1407928126427758733", "type": 0, "author_id": "183782216353054720", "author_name": "omnichromia", "author_bot": false, "content": "personally I'd like to cast one vote in favor of ② being changed to match ③.\nespecially in the case of \"Ace Up My Sleeves\", as the word \"Trump\" in the west now unfortunately has a *very* different connotation if not followed immediately by \"Card\"; and even then, I think it'd be preferable to not have that thought be evoked in a game we play to escape those kinds of things.", "timestamp": "2025-08-21T04:23:54.554000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1407928126427758733", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Scene Title Cards", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1407945533955248288", "channel_id": "1407928126427758733", "type": 0, "author_id": "1376763322568937562", "author_name": "morimens_15", "author_bot": false, "content": "Ahhh yes, about this:\n\nThe smaller English text in cursive were ancient machine translations of the titles, added by our Chinese speaking writers. Back then they wanted some decorative text on there so it looked prettier 😹 \n\nOn the other hand, the Larger Title text in the middle may not have the best translation either: Those strings were all machine translated, and many were so extremely long that they looked very ugly on the game interface.\n\nSo I mass edited them to 1) make sure they're all capitalized in the title format, and 2) make sure they don't go over ~25 characters that they break the interface", "timestamp": "2025-08-21T04:32:53.658000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-08-21T04:38:11.338000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1407928126427758733", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Scene Title Cards", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1407946152879587379", "channel_id": "1407928126427758733", "type": 0, "author_id": "1376763322568937562", "author_name": "morimens_15", "author_bot": false, "content": "So:\n\n1) I can ask for our UI designer's help to remove ① and ③ from the multilanguage version interface. So people only see ②.\nBecause the sheets are formatted in a way that ① and ③ aren't accessible to translators (not even me...) so we can't really edit those ancient machine translations. Best thing we can do is probably just remove them for the time being.\n\n2) When the current translation of ②, the main big text title, isn't really ideal, we edit it to make it read better.", "timestamp": "2025-08-21T04:35:21.221000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-08-21T04:37:29.616000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1407928126427758733", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Scene Title Cards", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1407947739156971620", "channel_id": "1407928126427758733", "type": 0, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "Understood! I figured that was likely the case, so I've been translating the stage titles as I go along to try and keep them as accurate as possible (and updating the english term sheets with my suggested changes as well since most of the stage titles show up in there).\n\nI wasn't aware of the 25-character limit, but I'll do another pass afterwards to make sure nothing gets excessively long. I'll cross-reference the edited stage titles afterwards across the entire sheet to try and make sure I catch all instances of each, since they show up multiple times", "timestamp": "2025-08-21T04:41:39.419000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-08-21T04:42:05.177000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "❤️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1407928126427758733", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Scene Title Cards", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1407948113452204034", "channel_id": "1407928126427758733", "type": 0, "author_id": "183782216353054720", "author_name": "omnichromia", "author_bot": false, "content": "-# just gonna add that \"Ace Up My Sleeve\" is only 16 characters so it fits\n-# ok that's all from me bye", "timestamp": "2025-08-21T04:43:08.658000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "❤️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1407928126427758733", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Scene Title Cards", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1407948349096853554", "channel_id": "1407928126427758733", "type": 0, "author_id": "88644018673582080", "author_name": "arkaether", "author_bot": false, "content": "yep that one i'm changing for sure, \"sleeved trump\" is a pretty bad literal MTL of the original cn text which is quite literally the idiom for \"ace up your sleeve\"", "timestamp": "2025-08-21T04:44:04.840000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "LUV", "emoji_id": "1003188300036702229", "count": 1}, {"emoji": "❤️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1407928126427758733", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Scene Title Cards", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1412867280844357813"]}
{"id": "1408095995535032400", "channel_id": "1408095995535032400", "type": 0, "author_id": "147364225411579904", "author_name": "strandiel", "author_bot": false, "content": "I'm a bit stuck what to do regarding translating names and unsure how to proceed properly. \n\nE.g. Daffodil, the flower, in German would be translated to Narzisse. Do I keep Daffodil, or do I translate to Narzisse. (Doll > Puppe etc)\n\nA bit different case of the alternate versions of characters like Tulu: Sovereign (Tulu: Herrscher/Souverän) where only the 2nd part has a meaning. \n\nInput from anyone would be greatly appreciated! Thank you in advance", "timestamp": "2025-08-21T14:30:46.494000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1408095995535032400", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "Name translations", "forum_channel_id": "1404748432328888401", "thread_tags": ["1404748529724952576", "1412867280844357813"], "is_thread_starter": true}
